The paper deals with the combinatorial and geometric properties of rectangular layouts, which are relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The concept of area-universal layouts is a novel and interesting contribution, which could also be of interest to researchers in discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The paper also mentions applications in cartography and VLSI design, which could place it in the sub-categories of graphics (cs.GR) and signal processing (cs.SI).
